==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|escarmouche||skirmish}}, from {{etyl|it|en}} {{m|it|scaramuccia}}, earlier {{m|it|schermugio}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈskɜː(r)mɪʃ/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# {{context|military|lang=en}} A brief [[battle]] between small groups, usually part of a longer or larger battle or [[war]].
# {{context|figuratively|lang=en}} By extension, any minor [[dispute]].
# A type of outdoor military style [[game]] using [[paintball]] or similar weapons.

